tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  39,57,"(Or should say) and that it will not say: (if Allah had but guided me) if Allah had showed me faith (I should have been among the dutiful) I would have been among those who believe in Allah's divine Oneness!"
  39,65,"(And verily it hath been revealed unto thee) in the Qur'an (as unto those before you) among the messengers ((saying): If thou ascribe a partner to Allah thy work will fail) in that state of idolatry (and thou indeed will be among the losers) in that you will be punished."